## ğŸš€ Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites
- **Arduino IDE** (version 1.8.x or newer)
- **ESP32 Board Package** for Arduino IDE
- **LiquidCrystal Library** (usually pre-installed)
- **USB Cable** (USB-C or Micro-USB depending on ESP32 board)

### Arduino IDE Setup
1. **Install ESP32 Board Package**:
   - Go to File â†’ Preferences
   - Add this URL to Additional Board Manager URLs:
     ```
     https://dl.espressif.com/dl/package_esp32_index.json
     ```
   - Go to Tools â†’ Board â†’ Board Manager
   - Search "ESP32" and install "ESP32 by Espressif Systems"

2. **Select Board and Port**:
   - Tools â†’ Board â†’ ESP32 Arduino â†’ ESP32 Dev Module
   - Tools â†’ Port â†’ Select your ESP32 port

### Hardware Setup
1. **Power Connections**:
   ```
   ESP32 VIN  â†’ 5V Power Supply
   ESP32 GND  â†’ Ground (common)
   ```

2. **LCD Connections** (16x2 with I2C or parallel):
   ```
   LCD RS  â†’ GPIO 36    LCD D4 â†’ GPIO 26
   LCD EN  â†’ GPIO 35    LCD D5 â†’ GPIO 27  
   LCD D0  â†’ Not used   LCD D6 â†’ GPIO 28
   LCD RW  â†’ Ground     LCD D7 â†’ GPIO 29
   LCD VSS â†’ Ground     LCD A  â†’ 5V
   LCD VDD â†’ 5V         LCD K  â†’ Ground
   LCD V0  â†’ Potentiometer (contrast)
   ```

3. **Motor Driver Connections**:
   ```
   L298N IN1 â†’ GPIO 8     Motor A â†’ Door Motor +
   L298N IN2 â†’ GPIO 9     Motor B â†’ Door Motor -
   L298N ENA â†’ GPIO 10    VCC â†’ 12V Power
   L298N GND â†’ Ground     GND â†’ Ground
   ```

4. **Button and LED Connections**:
   ```
   Buttons: GPIO 38,39 (with 10kÎ© pull-down resistors)
   LEDs: GPIO 43,44,45,46 (with 220Î© current limiting resistors)
   Status LED: GPIO 31 (with 220Î© resistor)
   ```

### Software Installation
1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Emir196/esp32-door-control-system.git
   ```
2. Open `door_control_system.ino` in Arduino IDE
3. Select your ESP32 board and port
4. Upload the code to your ESP32

